The paper discusses the development of an executable model of a railway interlocking system and the verification of safety properties using model checking. This involves software engineering (cs.SE) techniques for building the model and translating application data, programming languages (cs.PL) for developing the tool, logic (cs.LO) for specifying safety properties, systems and control (cs.SY) for the railway domain, and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the use of automated verification techniques.
